---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import HeadingSmall from "@components/HeadingSmall.astro";
import TextLink from "@components/TextLink.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Xero | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Xero</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in New Zealand in 2006, Xero has grown into one of the world's
      leading online accounting platforms, helping over 3.5 million small
      business owners and their accountants manage their finances more easily.
      For many small businesses, Xero is the difference between staying on top
      of cash flow and scrambling through spreadsheets at tax time.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      In 2014, I joined a newly formed team in San Francisco as a Mobile Product
      Designer, focused on building Xero's payroll products across three
      continents. The challenge was bringing desktop-only payroll functionality
      to mobile, where business owners and employees needed quick access to
      time-off requests and payslips.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      As the first mobile team hire, I helped shape our team culture and product
      direction, working closely with the Director of Product Design to
      establish design patterns that would work across different markets and
      employment regulations.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Xero Me</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We inherited a product that had seen at least two unsuccessful launch
      attempts. Employees were still forced to log into an outdated web
      interface just to request time off, and managers had to remember to check
      their desktop computers to approve requests. Working with a product
      manager, engineers, and another designer, we had to understand what went
      wrong.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Learning from those past efforts, we simplified the experience and timed
      our release with XeroCon, Xero's annual conference. Instead of trying to
      replicate every desktop feature, we focused on what employees and managers
      actually needed on mobile: quick time-off requests and easy payslip
      access.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I contributed production iOS code, building a polished custom in-app
      notification toast to confirm time-off actions. One of my favorite
      achievements on the project.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-onboarding.png"
      alt="Employee onboarding flow introducing time-off request features."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Despite shipping pressure, I partnered with a researcher to run lean
      usability testing. I designed test scenarios and on-device prototypes
      while they handled recruitment, ensuring we could iron out the usability
      before launch.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      A key insight emerged: employees wanted to see the entire date range of
      their time-off requests filled in, not just start and end dates. This
      simple visual change made it immediately clear to both employees and
      managers exactly which days would be taken, reducing back-and-forth
      clarification.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-request.png"
      alt="Simplified leave request form with calendar integration and visual feedback."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-edit-request.png"
      alt="Request editing with full date range selection based on user research insights."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We launched mid-2015 across iOS and Android, announcing it at the
      following year's XeroCon to much fanfare. For the first time, business
      owners could approve time-off requests while away from their desk, and
      employees could submit requests without having to remember when they got
      back to the office.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Xero Me is now one of Xero's <TextLink
        target="_blank"
        href="https://www.xero.com/nz/xero-me/">core product offerings</TextLink
      >.
    </Text>
  </Group>
</Layout>
